article.headline: Cleveland St. 59, Wright St. 50
article.story: CLEVELAND -- Norris Cole scored 20 points to lead Cleveland State to a 59-50 victory over Wright State on Saturday night. But it was J'Nathan Bullock's 10 points during an 18-0 run that woke up Cleveland State and drove the Vikings to an insurmountable 35-17 lead at halftime. Bullock finished with 14 points for Cleveland State (13-9, 6-5 Horizon League). Troy Tabler had 12 points for Wright State (15-8, 6-5). Wright State jumped to a 10-4 lead before Bullock rocked Cleveland State out of its sluggish start. Bullock hit two 3-pointers, a layup and a pair for free throws in that 18-0 run while Wright State, which had won five straight, went scoreless for nearly 7 minutes.
